      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Hanuš Gibian, which became a part of the Documentation campaign, Prague.
          Gibian was imprisoned together with his wife and son in the Nováky labour camp in
          Slovakia. In the autumn of 1944, during the Slovak National Uprising they got away from
          the camp. Afterwards they were hiding in the mountains near Banská Bystrica. In November
          1944 they were caught by the German troops. Gibian describes the execution of more than
          forty Jews. He was shot and survived only due to the fact, that he pretended to be
          death.</p>
      </abstract>
